The paper discusses Bayesian active learning and experimental design problems, which are commonly studied in the fields of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also applies the algorithm to active localization using a robot manipulator, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses decision making, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper uses mathematical tools such as homogeneous symmetric polynomials, which are commonly studied in the field of discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science (cs.DS).
